abstract: Proposals from investors seeking to shake up Tesla’s board and force Mr. Musk to give up one of his two top positions were rejected.

abstract: Several prominent chief executives are considering running for president. But “the history of business leaders in the White House has not been good.”

lead_paragraph: Since Donald Trump was unexpectedly elected president on Nov. 8, 2016, speculation has swirled about whether another well-known business leader might make a bid for the White House in 2020.

abstract: A new plan would overhaul much of the system in just a decade — if elected leaders can summon the will to make it happen.
snippet: A new plan would overhaul much of the system in just a decade — if elected leaders can summon the will to make it happen.
lead_paragraph: The Metropolitan Transportation Authority has long estimated that it could take half a century to make New York City’s neglected subway system reliable. What a relief, then, to hear that the man Gov. Andrew Cuomo hired to fix this festering mess recently announced a plan that clocks in at a mere 10 years. Yes, you read that right — the promise of a modern, fully functional subway within a decade.

abstract: Asked to revive troubled New York City schools, administrators have faced a flood of investigations that derail their efforts and, often, their careers.
snippet: Asked to revive troubled New York City schools, administrators have faced a flood of investigations that derail their efforts and, often, their careers.
lead_paragraph: When Nadav Zeimer became principal in 2010 of Harlem Renaissance High School, the school, which serves students who have fallen behind or dropped out of other schools, was failing. It had received a D on its most recent report card. At one point, New York City said it planned to close Harlem Renaissance and reopen it under a new name.

abstract: Mayor de Blasio’s wife, Chirlane McCray, hasn’t spent much time running New York’s nonprofit agency. It’s the least she could do.
snippet: Mayor de Blasio’s wife, Chirlane McCray, hasn’t spent much time running New York’s nonprofit agency. It’s the least she could do.
lead_paragraph: For more than a decade, New York City was governed by a billionaire known for reaching into his pocket to fund worthy causes and asking his wealthy friends to do the same.

abstract: New York City’s public housing system, the nation’s oldest and largest, stood out for its stability and good management. Now it is expected to get a federal monitor. What happened?
snippet: New York City’s public housing system, the nation’s oldest and largest, stood out for its stability and good management. Now it is expected to get a federal monitor. What happened?
lead_paragraph: As cities across the United States pulled back from towering public housing developments in the waning decades of the last century, New York City held firm.

abstract: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo said he wants to pay for a new subway overhaul plan by passing congestion pricing as Cynthia Nixon released her transit proposal.
snippet: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo said he wants to pay for a new subway overhaul plan by passing congestion pricing as Cynthia Nixon released her transit proposal.
lead_paragraph: It was a curious position: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo helped hire the new leader of New York City’s subway. But when that leader released a sweeping plan to fix the failing system last week, Mr. Cuomo offered a tepid response, promising simply to review it.

abstract: “Journeys” is a collection of 72 personal essays about how families from other countries started over in the United States.
snippet: “Journeys” is a collection of 72 personal essays about how families from other countries started over in the United States.
lead_paragraph: In “Journeys: An American Story” (RosettaBooks), Andrew Tisch and Mary Skafidas have compiled 72 essays by immigrants or their descendants, some of whom are famous, like Michael R. Bloomberg, while others are everyday — albeit exceptional — Americans. The diverse tales, presented together, show how immigrants have built and strengthened the culture of New York and the country at-large.
